	(
		'TXT_KEY_TRAIT_MC_CHINOOK',
		'Coastal Resources are automatically improved. [ICON_RES_MC_SALMON] Salmon and [ICON_RES_MC_ORCA] Orca may periodically migrate to and from Cities within range of the Coast; being more likely to migrate to Cities adjacent to Rivers.'
	),
	(
		'TXT_KEY_TRAIT_MC_CHINOOK_SHORT',
		'The Salmon Migrations'
	),
	(
		'TXT_KEY_RESOURCE_MC_ORCA',
		'Orca'
	),
	(
		'TXT_KEY_CIV5_RESOURCE_MC_ORCA_TEXT',
		'The Orca is a toothed whale belonging to the oceanic dolphin family. Orca are found in all oceans, from the frigid Arctic and Antarctic regions to tropical seas. Orca as a species have a diverse diet, although individual populations often specialize in particular types of prey. Some feed exclusively on fish, while others hunt marine mammals like pinnipeds, and even large whales. Orca are regarded as apex predators, lacking natural predators.'
	),
	(
		'TXT_KEY_RESOURCE_MC_SALMON',
		'Salmon'
	),
	(
		'TXT_KEY_CIV5_RESOURCE_MC_SALMON_TEXT',
		'The Chinook salmon is the largest species of Pacific salmon. Other commonly used names for the species include king salmon, Quinnat salmon, spring salmon, and Tyee salmon. Chinook are anadromous fish native to the north Pacific Ocean and the river systems of western North America, ranging from California to Alaska. They are also native to Asian rivers ranging from northern Japan to the Palyavaam River in the Siberian far east, although only the Kamchatka Peninsula supports relatively persistent native populations. They have been introduced to other parts of the world, including New Zealand and the Great Lakes. A large Chinook is a prized and sought-after catch for a sporting angler. The flesh of the salmon is also highly valued for its dietary nutritional content. Some populations are endangered, though Chinook salmon have not been assessed for the IUCN Red List.'
	),
	(
		'TXT_KEY_TRAIT_MC_CHINOOK_NOTIFICATION',
		'The {1_Resource} have migrated {2_Direction} {3_City}! '
	),
	(
		'TXT_KEY_TRAIT_MC_CHINOOK_AWAY',
		'away from'
	),
	(
		'TXT_KEY_TRAIT_MC_CHINOOK_TO',
		'to'
	),
--==========================================================================================================================
-- Plankhouse
--==========================================================================================================================
	(
		'TXT_KEY_CIV5_MC_PLANKHOUSE_TEXT',
		'In the Northwest, Native Americans lived in a shelter known as the Plankhouse. The Plankhouse was typically square or rectangular with one door and no windows. These houses varied in shape and design, however, according to the tribe that was building them. Because related families lived together in a Plankhouse, some large Plankhouses were as long as 100 feet. Each of these houses had a central cooking and living area and distinct private sections for sleeping areas.'
	),
	(
		'TXT_KEY_BUILDING_MC_PLANKHOUSE',
		'Plankhouse'
	),
	(
		'TXT_KEY_BUILDING_MC_PLANKHOUSE_HELP',
		'+1 [ICON_FOOD] Food from Ocean Tiles. Each source of [ICON_RES_FISH] Fish worked by this City produces +1 [ICON_FOOD] Food.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]When built next to a River, trade routes originating from this City produce an additional +2 [ICON_GOLD] Gold[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]City must be built next to a body of water.'
	),
	(
		'TXT_KEY_BUILDING_MC_PLANKHOUSE_DUMMY',
		'Plankhouse (Dummy)'
	),
	(
		'TXT_KEY_BUILDING_MC_PLANKHOUSE_DUMMY_HELP',
		'When built next to a River, trade routes originating from this City produce an additional +2 [ICON_GOLD] Gold.'
	),
	(
		'TXT_KEY_BUILDING_MC_PLANKHOUSE_STRATEGY',
		'The Plankhouse is the Chinookan unique replacement for the Lighthouse. Unlike the Lighthouse, the Plankhouse may be built in cities with access to any body of water (Coast, Ocean, River or Lake) and is unlocked earlier. When built next to a River it also increases the [ICON_GOLD] Gold yield of trade routes.'
	),
--==========================================================================================================================
-- Esquai-ah
--==========================================================================================================================
	(
		'TXT_KEY_UNIT_MC_CHINOOK_WHALER',
		'Esquai-ah'
	),
	(
		'TXT_KEY_CIV5_MC_CHINOOK_WHALER_TEXT',
		'The Chinook canoe had a raised prow which was often decorated with carved figures. These well-crafted canoes, which ranged from fifteen to fifty feet in length, were used in both freshwater and saltwater.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Chinook canoes were dugouts, created by hollowing out a single log, usually western red cedar. Before the introduction of metal tools, this was accomplished through fire, steam, and the use of wood and stone tools. It was a slow process—good canoes could take many weeks to make and thus were highly valued.[NEWLINE][NEWLINE]Lewis and Clark were impressed both with the Chinookan people''s canoe-making skills and with their ability to navigate the crafts under the worst conditions. While the Corps of Discovery was weathering a storm near the mouth of the Columbia in November 1805, Captain William Clark noted a group of Chinookans who were casually riding the waves in a small canoe packed with salmon to trade on the coast. After speaking briefly with the stranded explorers, the Indian party headed across the estuary through what Clark described as "the highest Sees I ever Saw a Small vestle ride." He referred to them as "Certainly the best Canoe navigaters I ever Saw."'
	),
	(
		'TXT_KEY_UNIT_MC_CHINOOK_WHALER_STRATEGY',
		'The Esquai-ah is the Chinookan Unique Workboat. Rather than building Fishing Boats like its civilian counterpart, the Esquai-ah is a ranged naval unit that retreats before combat. It can prevent sources of [ICON_RES_MC_SALMON] Salmon and [ICON_RES_MC_ORCA] Orca from migrating away when stationed on them and can repair any pillaged coastal improvements. It is also much cheaper to construct than the Workboat.'
	),
	(
		'TXT_KEY_UNIT_HELP_MC_CHINOOK_WHALER',
		'A Ranged Naval Unit that retreats before combat. This Unit prevents sources of [ICON_RES_MC_SALMON] Salmon and [ICON_RES_MC_ORCA] Orca from migrating away when stationed on them. Only the Chinook may build it.'
	),
	(
		'TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_MC_CHINOOK_WHALER',
		'Whale Hunter'
	),
	(
		'TXT_KEY_PROMOTION_MC_CHINOOK_WHALER_HELP',
		'When when stationed on a source of [ICON_RES_MC_SALMON] Salmon or [ICON_RES_MC_ORCA] Orca the Unit will prevent the resource from migrating away.'
	);
